@{" Ruler Palette    " link RULR}  Quick access to options and items.
@ENDNODE


@NODE TOOL "Tool Palette"
The tool palette gives the user quick access to selecting the editors current
edit mode. These buttons are, from top to bottom :-


    @{B}Add@{UB}        Select ADD mode.
    @{B}Move@{UB}       Select MOVE mode.
    @{B}Drag@{UB}       Select DRAG mode.
    @{B}Polygon@{UB}    Select POLYGON mode.

    @{B}Edit@{UB}       Select EDIT mode.

    @{B}Delete@{UB}     Select DELETE mode.

    @{B}Magnify@{UB}    Select MAGNIFY mode.
@ENDNODE


@NODE EDIT "Edit Palette"
The edit palette displays useful information about the current edit operation.
This includes things like the length and angle of a wall etc. or the current map
position.
@ENDNODE


@NODE GRPH "Graphics Palette"
The graphics palette provides a representation of the currently selected graphic
in the texture palette, or on one of the edit panels. The display is not a true
representation of the original because it remaps a 256 colour image into the
number of colours the editors @{"screen mode" link DentEd:Help/Settings.Menu/SCRN} has available.
Therefore the more colours the editors screen has, the closer it looks to the
original graphic. Of course there has to be a trade of for this, and the main
one is speed of operation and also increased memory consumption.
@ENDNODE


@NODE INFO "Info Palette"
Sorry this option is either incomplete or unavailable to level designers at
