@ENDNODE


@NODE TEXT "Texture Palette"
The texture palette is the basis of all editing, the current edit mode (i.e.
walls, doors, objects) depicts what type of graphics are available and these
are displayed as a list of names in the palette. By hi-lighting a name and then
adding say a wall, the newly created wall is given the hi-lighted graphic as
it's basic image.

Some edit mode types support many types of graphics. For example walls can have
textures, patterns, windows or animations (not implemented see @{"Limitations" link DentEd:Help/DentEd.guide/LIMT})
whilst others like objects only have objects as graphics. You can switch between
these different graphic types using the T|P|W|A buttons located at the top of
the palette. Non-applicable buttons will be disabled if they have no relevance
to the current edit mode type.

    @{B}T@{UB}                - Shows Textures list
    @{B}P@{UB}                - Shows Patterns list
    @{B}W@{UB}                - Shows Windows list
    @{B}A@{UB}                - Shows Wall or Door Animations list (type dependant)

    @{B}Available/In Use@{UB} - Shows all available, or currently used ones
                       THIS OPTION IS CURRENTLY UNAVAILABLE DO NOT ATTEMPT TO USE!
@ENDNODE


