@NODE RULR "Ruler Palette"
The ruler palette gives the user quick access to often used options and in
particular the different item types. These buttons are, from left to right :-


    @{B}New@{UB}                         Create a new map, will confirm action.
    @{B}Open@{UB}                        Open an existing map.
    @{B}Save@{UB}                        Save map using the current name.

    @{B}Cut@{UB}                         Not implemented.
    @{B}Copy@{UB}                        Not implemented.
    @{B}Paste@{UB}                       Not implemented.
    @{B}Erase@{UB}                       Not implemented.

    @{B}Magnification@{UB}               Adjust the map view's magnification level.

    @{B}Wall Mode@{UB}                   Change default item type to WALLS.
    @{B}Door Mode@{UB}                   Change default item type to DOORS.
    @{B}Object Mode@{UB}                 Change default item type to FIXED OBJECTS.
    @{B}Transporter Mode@{UB}            Not implemented.
    @{B}Creature Mode@{UB}               Not implemented.
    @{B}Takeable Mode@{UB}               Not implemented.
    @{B}Set Player Position@{UB}         Set the players start position and direction.

    @{B}Define Players Environment@{UB}  Alter the levels/player environment.

    @{B}Test Map@{UB}                    Test the current map, must be saved first.
@ENDNODE
